Reclaim disk space: prune orphaned blobs and vacuum the database (Area 3)

Usage: hh gc [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --no-vacuum  Skip the (slow, disk-hungry) VACUUM; only prune orphaned blob files and stale rows. VACUUM rebuilds `hh.db` and needs temporary free space, so use this on a nearly-full disk
      --json       Emit machine-readable JSON instead of plain lines
  -h, --help       Print help

Example:
  hh gc
  hh gc --json
  hh gc --no-vacuum
